Sonny Perdue, the Secretary of Agriculture, reflects on his first year in office and discusses the Trump administration's commitment to rural America and the American farming industry. He highlights the administration's pro-growth policies, strong farm exports, and tax cuts that benefit farmers. Perdue also mentions the administration's efforts to eliminate burdensome regulations and address trade issues, particularly with China. He emphasizes the need for a farm bill that supports American farmers and ensures their competitiveness in the global market. Perdue concludes by expressing confidence in the administration's commitment to rural America and its efforts to support those who feed and clothe the world.